member.summary:
EF Core DbCommand interceptor that records every query as DB telemetry.
Register via:
services.AddDbContext<MyDbContext>(opts => opts.UseSqlite(conn).AddInterceptors(new AllStakDbCommandInterceptor()));

Delegating handler that captures outbound HttpClient calls — method, host, path, status, duration, request/response size — and records them as outbound telemetry in AllStak.
Usage:
builder.Services.AddHttpClient("default") .AddHttpMessageHandler<AllStakHttpHandler>(); builder.Services.AddTransient<AllStakHttpHandler>();

Wrap a job body in a using-block; success/failure heartbeat is sent on dispose.
Exceptions inside the block are re-thrown — the SDK never swallows user exceptions.


using (AllStakClient.Instance.Cron.Job("daily-report"))
{
    await GenerateReport();
}
